HCR 100 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Jackson
Requests the La. Gaming Control Bd. to ensure due diligence in proposed acquisitions that
encourage economic development, job creation, and benefits to the community of northwest
La.
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The Committee Amendments Proposed by House Committee on Administration of
Criminal Justice to the original bill:
1. Remove requests for economic plans, stakeholder meetings, public hearings, and
reports to the legislature regarding the potential sale of Sam's Town Hotel and
Casino to Bally's Corporation.
2. Provide that the legislature supports potential sales and acquisitions of gaming
facilities that will have a positive economic impact on the region.
